<h4> Guest registrations now available</h4>
<p>
JournalCon Austin is now accepting guest registrations for spouses and partners of attendees.
 A guest registration costs $20 and allows the guest access to all EVENING events. Guests who 
 wish to attend panels and sessions during the day should register for JournalCon as regular 
 attendees.
 </p>
 <p>
 <b>
Guest registrations will be accepted through 11:59 pm CST on Monday, September 15.
</b>
</p>
<p>
A guest must be registered by an attendee who has completed and paid for his/her registration
 already. We will not accept guest registrations from non-attendees.
 </p>
 <p>
Attendees should do the following in order to register a guest:
</p>
<p>
1. Send an email to jcon@journalcon.austin-stories.com with the words "guest registration" 
in the subject line. The email message must contain the following information:
</p>
<ul>
<li>Attendee's real first and last name (this is the name under which your registration 
is kept in our database)</li>
<li>Attendee's email address</li>
<li>Guest's real first and last name</li>
<li>Guest's preferred badge name</li>
<li>Guest's email address</li>
<li>Whether you will pay via check or PayPal</li>
</ul>
<p>
2. Send either a check or PayPal payment for $20, immediately after you send the email message.
If you are sending payment via PayPal, go to <a href="https://www.paypal.com/cgi-bin/webscr?cmd=_xclick&amp;business=devota@devota.org&amp;item_name=JournalCon+2003&amp;no_shipping=1" target="_blank">
our PayPal link</a> to submit a payment for $20.
</p>
<p>
If you are sending a check, <b>we must receive it by September 15</b>. Make checks payable 
to JournalCon Austin: Web Writers Weekend and send to the following address:
</p>
<p>
<b>
PO Box 685083<br />
Austin, TX 78768-5083
</b>
</p>
<p>
Please contact us if you have any questions.
</p>


